Get events of ACS system

The Get-AcsEvent cmdlet gets events of ACS system. Use the parameters of Get- AcsEvent to search for events by using filter values. Get- AcsEvent gets only the events that match all of the specified filter values.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: $May31 = get-date 5/31/2016 $July1 = get-date 7/01/2016 Get-ACSEvent -ResourceGroupName system -FarmName default -StartTime $May31 -endTime $July1 Get-ACSEvent -AdminUri $adminUri -ResourceGroupName system -FarmName default -StartTime $May31 -endTime $July1 -NodeName testNode Get-ACSEvent -ResourceGroupName system -FarmName default -StartTime $May31 -endTime $July1 -ProviderGuid "F56977D7-986C-4F3D-98CB-A11BB5F00996" Get-ACSEvent -ResourceGroupName system -FarmName default -StartTime $May31 -endTime $July1 -NodeName testNode -ProviderGuid "F56977D7-986C-4F3D-98CB-A11BB5F00996"
